						<tr>
							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal"><span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="color: Orange"><span style="text-decoration: underline">F.A.Q.</span></span></span></span>
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="color: Orange">Who can use poisons?</span></span>
<br />
Predators and Rogues who are level 10+. This is when they receive the Poisoning skill. Note that when Predators and Rogues receive the Poisoning skill, it will be at level 50 so Poisons which cap at 50 will not be terribly effective.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="color: Orange">What do poisons do?</span></span>
<br />
Poisons can either do damage or debuff. It is possible for each player to have one damage poison and one debuff poison stick at the same time. While the debuff poisons can reduce resistance to slashing, piercing, divine, heat, cold, etc., but most importantly you can lower poison resistance with a debuffing poison!
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="color: Orange">What is the most effective way to use poison?</span></span>
<br />
The most common thing to debuff on an opponent is their poison resistance so the damage poison will stick more often and then use a high DOT poison. Only one poison will stick at a time so if you are made out of platinum and can find the ingredients for the rare poisons the all-up-front-with-no-DOT poisons can be used in tandem with a high DOT poison in an effort to boost Proc rates and add in the occasional higher damage Proc. 
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="color: Orange">Where do I get poisons?</span></span>
<br />
The most common place is to either make it yourself (Scholar's can make the lower level ones) or a friend who is a Scholar or Alchemist. The player-made poisons are much more effective than the NPC-sold ones. If you don't want to make your own and cannot find someone to make them for you, you can find them from Alchmists such as the troll woman in Freeport in the middle of Scaleyard and in Qeynos from the Alchemist Shop.
<br />
[ <span style="font-style: italic">Note: if you know the NPC names and/or locs please post them here so I can update this document. Thx~! </span> ]
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="color: Orange">When would I want to use poison?</span></span>
<br />
Any time you aren't pulling too much hate. Especially with the addition of the poison deduffing poison its possible to do horrendous damage and a corresponding amount of hate. As a 17 Predator using player-made poison conning orange and a poison-resistance debuffing poison I fairly regularly did over 50pts of just poison damage with Back Shot and another 100-118pts of poison damage with Open Shot. Add in the DOT (damage over time) and you can see its great when solo'ing but can make the tanks ability to hold hate tough when grouping if the scout isn't careful!
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="color: Orange">How do I use poison?</span></span>
<br />
While this may be old news to many, there are many more who don't know. To use a poison Attune it, then 'Equip' the vial into one of your two Activatable slots. Then right-click on the vial and choose 'Use' to cast the poison like a spell. It will display a yellow symbol in your Active Spells window. If you are using a damage and debuff poison at the same time make sure they both stay active since damage poisons usually stick 100 times ("100 Procs") before wearing off while Debuff poisons only last for 40 Procs.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="color: Orange">How do I tell that my poison is working?</span></span>
<br />
If you look at the numbers above your targets head, the spell-DOT and Poison damage will have a 'glow' around it. A given poison at a given level of the poisoning skill will do the same damage when it works, and poison resistance on the mob will either allow it to Resist the damage or keep the Poison from Proc'ing at all. 
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="color: Orange">How does my Poisoning skill factor in to the poison? Don't posions have a set damage?</span></span>
<br />
Poisons that con orange to you stick muuuch better than white or gray ones. This is the most important reason to use a poison that cons well for your level. If the poison is gray to you then your effective poisoning skill will be limited by the Mastery poisoning level of the poison thus capping an already poor ability to stick. Just say 'no' to gray poisons!  
<br />

<br />
Note that some scouts will use several damaging poisons to increase the chance of one Proc'ing. While only one can be in effect at a time, the chance for each to proc is attractive, but if you use a Poison-resistance debuffing poison you'll see a single high damage poison rip through opponents much more frequently!
<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal"><span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="color: Orange"><span style="text-decoration: underline">Common Pitfalls</span></span></span></span><ul><span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="color: Orange">PITFALL: Multiple damage poisons no longer stack</span></span>. 
<br />
- Poisons used to layer one upon another as long as they were a different color vial. Now only one damage poison and one debuff poison will work at the same time from each scout.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="color: Orange">PITFALL: When in a group make sure your color of vial differs from the other scouts</span></span>.
<br />
 - When multiple scouts poison a target, they must use different color vials of poison. Some vials are red, green, blue, light blue, purple, etc. Make sure to carry two different colors of poison if you will be grouping so the group DPS can stay high.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="color: Orange">PITFALL: I can't afford poison</span></span>! 
<br />
- A top-notch starting poison with a Poisoning 200 Mastery will con orange for quite a while. On my server, Befallen, these run 3gp/vial. A pristine-made ("Translucent") poison has 7 uses each worth 100 Procs or 12 hours. If you exp the whole time and use Yellow-Orange poisons you WILL use all 100 Procs, so the time limit is moot. At 3gp/7 uses you're paying 42.8 silver for each 100 Procs and that comes to roughly 43 copper per 50+ boost to your damage. At low levels this can be a lot of money to be spending, but how much is the food and drink you'll lose the use of if you die? How much time will you lose from running to get your shard and working off any exp debt? Its better to use a poor poison than no poison and best yet to use a good poison!
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="color: Orange">PITFALL: My Poison only lasted one hit then I had to recast it</span></span>!
<br />
- There are a few poisons, mainly debuffing poisons, that only Proc once before wearing. Always 'Examine' a poison to see how many times it will stick before having to be recast. These may have more utility in a Raid than in exp'ing.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="color: Orange">PITFALL: I tried them and Poisons suck</span></span>!
<br />
- Make sure you aren't using an NPC-poison like one of the Sludge variants. They are quite inferior to the player-made ones.
<br />
[Note from Gnume Awldewe:  Be aware, some players resell NPC poisons at a markup. These are easily distinguished by the look of the poison vial. NPC sold poisons have what looks like a String or a Fuse at the top.]</ul>
<br />

<br />

<br />
